      "content": "that makes sense for the economic side. for the second part of my debate, i also need to tackle the cultural argument. some historians suggest that segregation was defended as a way to preserve cultural integrity or community cohesion. \n\ncan you help me draft a few points for that? i need to argue from the perspective that separating communities allowed for the preservation of specific cultural identities and social norms without the friction of integration. how would someone argue that this \"cultural preservation\" was actually a benefit to the stability of society as a whole?",
